Once such announcements are scrutinised as part of the budget process, their early cost estimates need to be upwardly revised by an average of 25 per cent.

However, the poor cost performance of projects with early cost announcements is not just a warning to mistrust the infrastructure announcements of politicians. Rather, premature cost announcements appear to haunt projects throughout out their lives. After formal budget commitments, the costs of projects with early cost announcements project typically increase by a further 26 per cent (see \Vref{fig:projs-announced-early-have-larger-cost-overruns-at}).

