Another reason why early cost announcements often have a large overruns is that these low quality cost estimates are often imposed on the highest risk projects.
\Cref{fig:projs-announced-early-have-larger-cost-overruns-at} shows that projects with early cost estimates are substantially bigger, on average, than projects with later cost announcements. Section \ref{cost-estimates-should-reflect-predictable-patterns} of this report confirms that large projects are more prone to cost overruns than smaller projects in Australia, as is consistently the case internationally.

