\subsubsection*{An under-cooked election promise}

In 2002, the Federal Coalition Government committed to contributing \$12 million to the \$36 million cost of an upgrade to the Bruxner Highway in Northern New South Wales, to bypass Alstonville.\footcite{NSWHansardAlstonville} The following year, the then Labor Premier, Bob Carr, promised in a New South Wales election campaign to build the bypass by the end of 2006, at a cost of \$36 million.\footcite{ABCNews2003PlanforBruxnerHighway}

